  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Capacity Building Support to the Department of Social Welfare and Development (DSWD) Towards Protection of Mobile and Fragile Populations in the Philippines</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In its efforts to manage and promote safe and orderly migration, the International Organisation for Migration (IOM) is the co-lead of the Camp Coordination and Camp Management (CCCM) cluster in natural disasters at the global-level. IOM is also an active member of the Shelter Cluster and has taken a leading role in numerous humanitarian shelter programs in the Philippines and across the world. As the co-leadfor CCCM in the Philippines, and as a leading contributor to the shelterresponses for Typhoon Haiyan and the Marawi Crisis, IOM aims to strengthen the CCCM, shelter and displacement tracking capacity of the Department of Social Welfare and Development (DSWD) at the National, Regional and Field Office levels. This will help the government prepare for and respond effectively to humanitarian crises with strong technicalcapacity, coordination and accountability. In order to do so, IOM will strengthen the DSWD&apos;s CCCM and Shelter response capacity through training of camp managers from national to local levels and the development of a shelter strategy.</narrative>
  </description>
